Rating: 4
This recipe was just the coffee cake I was looking for to serve with coffee on short notice. The yogurt made it perfectly rich and textured not unlike a scone. I did add salt and did not add the apple. I had to use margarine. I needed it to bake more quickly so I halved the recipe and baked in in a metal cake pan with the streusel as an inside layer and as topping. I had to turn the temp down to 325 part way through cooking, but it did take at least 10 minutes off the bake time. I came out perfectly and received rave reviews. I will certainly make it again whenever I want coffee cake.

Rating: 4
I have made this recipe many times, and everybody loves it. I do add a teaspoon of salt to the flour mixture. I also add about a 1/2 cup of chopped nuts to the filling. Sometimes I omitt the apple. When I do include the apple I shred it first. I bake the batter in one bundt pan with only one layer of filling at 325 degrees for about 55 min. It comes out golden with a delicious nut center. Also make sure you don't over mix.

Rating: 3
I used margarine instead of unsalted butter in the batter, and added 1 tsp. cinnamon with the nutmeg. I baked it in a bundt pan, and made 3 layers with the batter and filling. The result was very tasty, moist and light.

