Rating: 4
I only made half the recipe. I used Dannon strawberry yogurt (not fruit on the bottom) instead of plain, and it turned out good. It is so delicious! It is very moist too!

Rating: 2
This is a good quick recipe. With some simple changes it could be great. Try these alterations: Add 1/2 cup of finely chopped walnuts to the streusel. Try vanilla yogurt instead of plain. Add icing, a basic powdered sugar and milk icing will work fine. Finally, try making half a recipe; you'll only have to throw out a half an egg and one loaf is pretty big. I got 10 thick slices from one.

Rating: 4
This recipe does well in a bundt pan using the same recipe. It is good for one bundt pan. I would recommend a nice coffee icing (of your choice) on top of the cake.